Natural disasters can strike at any time so it's important to be prepared. Here are some tips: [link to image of natural disaster preparedness kit]
Floods are one of the most common natural disasters. If you live in an area that is prone to flooding be sure to have a plan in place. [link to image of flood preparedness plan]
Wildfires are another common natural disaster. If you live in an area that is prone to wildfires be sure to create a defensible space around your home. [link to image of wildfire defensible space]
Earthquakes can happen anywhere in the world so it's important to know what to do if one strikes. [link to image of earthquake safety tips]

Hurricanes are powerful storms that can cause major damage. If you live in an area that is prone to hurricanes be sure to have a hurricane evacuation plan. [link to image of hurricane evacuation plan]

Tornadoes are brief but powerful storms that can cause significant damage. If you live in an area that is prone to tornadoes be sure to have a tornado shelter plan. [link to image of tornado shelter plan]

Volcanic eruptions can cause a variety of hazards including ash falls lava flows and pyroclastic flows. If you live in an area near a volcano be sure to have a volcano eruption plan. [link to image of volcano eruption plan]

Droughts can cause a variety of problems including water shortages crop failures and wildfires. If you live in an area that is prone to droughts be sure to have a drought preparedness plan. [link to image of drought preparedness plan]

Extreme heat can be dangerous especially for the elderly and those with chronic health conditions. If you live in an area that experiences extreme heat be sure to have a heat wave preparedness plan. [link to image of heat wave preparedness plan]

Extreme cold can also be dangerous especially for the elderly and those with chronic health conditions. If you live in an area that experiences extreme cold be sure to have a cold weather preparedness plan. [link to image of cold weather preparedness plan]
